{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.78",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 78,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 78 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:1",
      "text": "Give ear, O my people, to my teaching; incline your ears to the words of my mouth!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:2",
      "text": "I will open my mouth in a parable; I will utter dark sayings from of old,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:3",
      "text": "things that we have heard and known, that our fathers have told us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:4",
      "text": "We will not hide them from their children, but tell to the coming generation the glorious deeds of the Lord, and his might, and the wonders which he has wrought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:5",
      "text": "He established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers to teach to their children;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:6",
      "text": "that the next generation might know them, the children yet unborn, and arise and tell them to their children,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:7",
      "text": "so that they should set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:8",
      "text": "and that they should not be like their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation, a generation whose heart was not steadfast, whose spirit was not faithful to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:9",
      "text": "The Ephraimites, armed with the bow, turned back on the day of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:10",
      "text": "They did not keep God's covenant, but refused to walk according to his law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:11",
      "text": "They forgot what he had done, and the miracles that he had shown them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:12",
      "text": "In the sight of their fathers he wrought marvels in the land of Egypt, in the fields of Zoan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:13",
      "text": "He divided the sea and let them pass through it, and made the waters stand like a heap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:14",
      "text": "In the daytime he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a fiery light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:15",
      "text": "He cleft rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink abundantly as from the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:16",
      "text": "He made streams come out of the rock, and caused waters to flow down like rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:17",
      "text": "Yet they sinned still more against him, rebelling against the Most High in the desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:18",
      "text": "They tested God in their heart by demanding the food they craved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:19",
      "text": "They spoke against God, saying, “Can God spread a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:20",
      "text": "He smote the rock so that water gushed out and streams overflowed. Can he also give bread, or provide meat for his people?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:21",
      "text": "Therefore, when the Lord heard, he was full of wrath; a fire was kindled against Jacob, his anger mounted against Israel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:22",
      "text": "because they had no faith in God, and did not trust his saving power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:23",
      "text": "Yet he commanded the skies above, and opened the doors of heaven;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:24",
      "text": "and he rained down upon them manna to eat, and gave them the grain of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:25",
      "text": "Man ate of the bread of the angels; he sent them food in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:26",
      "text": "He caused the east wind to blow in the heavens, and by his power he led out the south wind;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:27",
      "text": "he rained flesh upon them like dust, winged birds like the sand of the seas;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:28",
      "text": "he let them fall in the midst of their camp, all around their habitations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:29",
      "text": "And they ate and were well filled, for he gave them what they craved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:30",
      "text": "But before they had sated their craving, while the food was still in their mouths,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:31",
      "text": "the anger of God rose against them and he slew the strongest of them, and laid low the picked men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:32",
      "text": "In spite of all this they still sinned; despite his wonders they did not believe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:33",
      "text": "So he made their days vanish like a breath, and their years in terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:34",
      "text": "When he slew them, they sought for him; they repented and sought God earnestly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:35",
      "text": "They remembered that God was their rock, the Most High God their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:36",
      "text": "But they flattered him with their mouths; they lied to him with their tongues.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:37",
      "text": "Their heart was not steadfast toward him; they were not true to his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:38",
      "text": "Yet he, being compassionate, forgave their iniquity, and did not destroy them; he restrained his anger often, and did not stir up all his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:39",
      "text": "He remembered that they were but flesh, a wind that passes and comes not again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:40",
      "text": "How often they rebelled against him in the wilderness and grieved him in the desert!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:41",
      "text": "They tested him again and again, and provoked the Holy One of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:42",
      "text": "They did not keep in mind his power, or the day when he redeemed them from the foe;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:43",
      "text": "when he wrought his signs in Egypt, and his miracles in the fields of Zoan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:44",
      "text": "He turned their rivers to blood, so that they could not drink of their streams.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:45",
      "text": "He sent among them swarms of flies, which devoured them, and frogs, which destroyed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:46",
      "text": "He gave their crops to the caterpillar, and the fruit of their labor to the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:47",
      "text": "He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycamores with frost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:48",
      "text": "He gave over their cattle to the hail, and their flocks to thunderbolts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:49",
      "text": "He let loose on them his fierce anger, wrath, indignation, and distress, a company of destroying angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:50",
      "text": "He made a path for his anger; he did not spare them from death, but gave their lives over to the plague.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:51",
      "text": "He smote all the first-born in Egypt, the first issue of their strength in the tents of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:52",
      "text": "Then he led forth his people like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:53",
      "text": "He led them in safety, so that they were not afraid; but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.54",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:54",
      "text": "And he brought them to his holy land, to the mountain which his right hand had won.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.55",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:55",
      "text": "He drove out nations before them; he apportioned them for a possession and settled the tribes of Israel in their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.56",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:56",
      "text": "Yet they tested and rebelled against the Most High God, and did not observe his testimonies,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.57",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:57",
      "text": "but turned away and acted treacherously like their fathers; they twisted like a deceitful bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.58",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:58",
      "text": "For they provoked him to anger with their high places; they moved him to jealousy with their graven images.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.59",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:59",
      "text": "When God heard, he was full of wrath, and he utterly rejected Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.60",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:60",
      "text": "He forsook his dwelling at Shiloh, the tent where he dwelt among men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.61",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:61",
      "text": "and delivered his power to captivity, his glory to the hand of the foe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.62",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:62",
      "text": "He gave his people over to the sword, and vented his wrath on his heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.63",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:63",
      "text": "Fire devoured their young men, and their maidens had no marriage song.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.64",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword, and their widows made no lamentation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.65",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:65",
      "text": "Then the Lord awoke as from sleep, like a strong man shouting because of wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.66",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:66",
      "text": "And he put his adversaries to rout; he put them to everlasting shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.67",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:67",
      "text": "He rejected the tent of Joseph, he did not choose the tribe of Ephraim;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.68",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 68,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:68",
      "text": "but he chose the tribe of Judah, Mount Zion, which he loves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.78.69",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 69,
